    <h1 style="color: darkred;">About Trigun</h1>

    <p style="font-size: 18px;">
        Trigun is a manga and anime from 1998. It was created by Yasuhiro Nightow and the main themes
        revolve around morality and the value of a life. This is a sci-fi, futuristic western that takes place on a 
        desert planet known as Gunsmoke, or No Man's Land.  The main character is Vash the Stampede, with the main
        supporting character being Wolfwood. The antagonist is named, Nai or also Knives. He is the main character's twin
        brother. Vash The Stampede is a wanted criminal with a bounty of sixty billion double dollars on his head. He is a pacifist gunman,
        who refuses to kill at all costs.
    </p>

    <p style="font-size: 18px;">
        I do prefer the manga, book version, of Trigun than its two aninmated counterparts. The first anime was released in 1998
        which is closer to the source material but deviates later in the series. The later anime was released in 2023, and was
        described as a retelling of the main events. However, out of the two animes, I do like the older one more than the newer one.
        The older one resembes the story I fell in love with moreso than the newer one. I also like to collect figures and plushies
        from this series.
    </p>

